<mod:findName type="event" name="LAST_STAND_START_2">
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="unique_vance" blue="true">
		<text>(Vance Prime) Contact Tully.</text>
		<event load="FR_TULLY_CONTACT_VANCE"/>
	</mod-append:choice>
</mod:findName>

<event name="FR_TULLY_CONTACT_VANCE">
	<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. Tully's expression is in clear shock at the sight of your crew. His eyes can be seen flooding with endless disbelief, disdain and pure, unadulterated confusion, and he stays silent for several minutes. The rest of the officers remain still, awkwardly staring at him and back at you, waiting for whatever order Tully might give to them. Suddenly, Tully speaks up... or rather, he shouts out. "...VANCE?! What the hell are you doing here?!"</text>
		<variable name="loc_fr_vance_peaceful" op="add" val="1"/>
		<choice hidden="true" blue="false">
			<text>Before you can speak, Admiral Vance steps forward into the vidscreen, lightly pushing you away off camera. He stares down at his old friend, his expression contorting similarly to the Admiral's. "Brodric Tully, it truly has been ages, hasn't it?" He speaks in a tone that can be seen as remorseful, smug and elated all at once.</text> 
			<event>
				<text>With his fists clenched, Tully finally gathers the strength needed to compose himself as his eyes focus squarely on Vance. "Vance Wentworth, I have absolutely no idea why you are here in person. Much less, from what I can gather from the log of your ship, why you have been working with Federation soldiers for the past month? I have no idea what made you switch sides, unless this is all just a ploy. But.. we have no time for finger-pointing or deliberations over our past, we can do that later. Right now, the biggest threat is the Flagship currently on its way to the Capitol. 
				
				If you truly are working for our side and didn't tell your men to stand down, then I assume that can only mean they're not following your orders anymore. I do, however, hope you can peacefully resolve this. If you can somehow manage to get the Flagship to stand down, I will make sure that their crew have a fair trial. I fully expect you to betray me again, Vance. Please, for everyone's sake... prove me wrong."</text>
				<choice hidden="true" blue="false">
					<text>Vance nods as he shuts down the call, muttering under his breath as he moved back to his post. "I won't, Tully... not again... never again..."</text>
					<event load="LASTSTAND_EMPTY_BEACON"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
</event>

<mod:findName type="event" name="BOSS_TEXT_1">
	<mod-append:choice hidden="true" req="unique_vance">
		<text>(Vance Prime) Contact the Flagship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Flagship doesn't take long to notice you. Before it can lock on its weapons, Vance Prime hails the Rebel fleet, speaking to its local Vance.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="FR_FLAGSHIP_VANCE"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</mod-append:choice>
</mod:findName>

<event name="FR_FLAGSHIP_VANCE">
	<text>The other Vance appears shocked when he sees Vance Prime on the other end. He opens his mouth to talk, but Vance Prime stops him. "Admiral Vance, I understand what your orders were, but... they don't matter anymore. Surrender peacefully, and I will ensure you and your crew will be treated fairly."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The opposing Vance stares at yours for a few minutes, contemplating the best course of action. "And how can you guarantee this? How can I know that this isn't a trap?"</text>
				<choice req="loc_fr_vance_peaceful" lvl="1" blue="true" hidden="true">
					<text>"Admiral Tully himself gave me this task."</text>
					<event load="FR_FLAGSHIP_VANCE_SUCCESS"/>
				</choice>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>"My word should be enough."</text>
					<event>
						<text>The other Vance doesn't buy his response and shakes his head. "I'm afraid it isn't, Prime. You know deep down that combat is inevitable. Now come, let us duel!"</text>
						<choice hidden="true">
							<text>Continue...</text>
							<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
						</choice>
					</event>
				</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_FLAGSHIP_VANCE_SUCCESS">
	<text>You watch on as Vance is left staring at Prime, trying to understand his own thoughts and what would lead him to make such a request. Eventually, and much to the disbelief of the entire crew, Vance nods his head. "Very well, Vance Prime. We offer our surrender. I hope, for the sake of this reality, that you know what you're doing."</text>
	<achievement silent="false">ACH_FR_EVENT_VANCE_PEACE</achievement>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<win ach="peace" creditsText="credit_victory_peace" text="Your peaceful display was unexpected, but welcome." creditsBackground="VICTORY_PEACE"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

